occurrenceRemarks: Found by J. Baker in brown turf algae (Zonaria), collected under permit by D. Kinasz for SACReD, at 15m deep, Gulf St Vincent. Identified by D. Staples, Museum Victoria. This damaged specimen with 4 legs missing is the second example of P. gowlettae known, and also the first live specimen. The type specimen was found in 1978, in a sample of macroalgae collected by SA Shepherd at Elliston, in western SA. Body = 1cm long; legs = 3cm long.
